ibis.expr.api.Expr.execute¶

Expr.execute(limit='default', async=False, params=None)¶

If this expression is based on physical tables in a database backend, execute it against that backend.

Parameters:

limit : integer or None, default ‘default’

Pass an integer to effect a specific row limit. limit=None means “no limit”. The default is whatever is in ibis.options.
Returns:

result : expression-dependent

Result of compiling expression and executing in backend
